<p><em>Father Time</em> kept us from putting the "super" in Flagstaff today. But such prefix privations do little to dampen our spirits.</p>
<p>It was cooler than expected at the start, so both of us did our respective about-faces in order to grab an extra layer for the descent.</p>
<p>As is always the case, however, we warmed quickly on Baseline, and by Gregory Canyon we were like steamed lobsters (with rubber bands around our claws).</p>
<p>No rubber bands on Dave's freshly tuned bike, though. Indeed, a big "thank you" to Eric for neutralizing that squeaking noise. I think it was actually Dave's knees, not the old crankset.</p>
